    "body": "> you mean geth will accept a transaction with such V - value on a mainnet ?\r\n\r\nIt will not accept such values on mainnet (where the chain id has to be 1), but may accept them if the chain ID is different. [Relevant geth code](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/33ca98ece985f5085ac8ec19a49239d726850004/core/types/transaction.go?plain=1#L203-L227).\r\n\r\nSmall question: why is the test called `RightVRSTestF0000000a`? I don't see F0000000a being featured anywhere (`v` is 0xf028 = 61480). In the F0000000a it's 0xf029, etc.\r\n\r\nWhat's the point of these tests actually (and why so many of them)?",
